<html extends="IdePage">
<head title="New layer"/>

<body>
   <div id="content">
      <div id="pageContent" exec="server">
         <div id="sectionContent">
            <h2>New layer</h2>
            Access the New-&gt;StrataCode layer dialog by right clicking on a directory in the bundles directory, the layers directory, or a layer group inside of one of those directories. Make sure the folder is a source folder of a StrataCode module in IntelliJ's project structure dialog. If that folder is already the currently selected folder, just use the File-&gt;New menu or the command-N shortcut<p/>
              <img class="centerImageBlock" src="/images/ide/chooseNewLayer.png" alt="New layer menu"/>
              <p/>
              Optionally specify a package. Choose whether this layer is always a dynamic layer, and whether all types, fields, methods are public by default. Click on Add... to add layers for this layer to extend.
              <img class="centerImageBlock" src="/images/ide/newLayer.png" alt="New layer"/>
              <p/>
         </div>
      </div>
   </div>
</body>
</html>
